---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Welcome to the Fabform.io Blog</h1>

      <p>
        Fabform.io is a powerful, developer‑friendly form backend designed for modern static sites,
        Jamstack projects, and lightweight web apps. Whether you're building with Astro, Eleventy,
        Hugo, Next.js, or plain HTML, Fabform.io gives you a fast, secure, and reliable way to
        collect form submissions without maintaining servers, databases, or custom APIs.
      </p>

      <p>
        This blog explores everything related to building better forms — from practical tutorials
        and integration guides to performance tips, UX patterns, and real‑world examples. If you're
        looking for the easiest way to add contact forms, signup forms, surveys, or lead‑capture
        workflows to your site, you're in the right place.
      </p>

      <h2>Why Developers Choose Fabform.io</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No backend required:</strong> Add a simple <code>action</code> URL and you're done.</li>
        <li><strong>Works with any static site generator:</strong> Astro, Eleventy, Hugo, Jekyll, and more.</li>
        <li><strong>Instant email notifications:</strong> Get alerts the moment a form is submitted.</li>
        <li><strong>Spam protection built‑in:</strong> Honeypots, rate‑limiting, and intelligent filtering.</li>
        <li><strong>Zero‑config setup:</strong> No servers, no databases, no maintenance.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What You’ll Find on This Blog</h2>
      <p>
        Our mission is to help developers ship forms faster and with more confidence. Expect deep‑dive
        tutorials, SEO‑friendly guides, and practical examples such as:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>How to add a contact form to your Astro site</li>
        <li>Best practices for static site form handling</li>
        <li>Improving form UX and conversion rates</li>
        <li>Security tips for handling user submissions</li>
        <li>Showcases of real projects using Fabform.io</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Whether you're a seasoned engineer or just getting started with static site development,
        Fabform.io helps you build forms that work — without the complexity.
      </p>

      <p><strong>Explore, learn, and build something great.</strong></p>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

